annotationA: Serine/threonine-protein phosphatase PP2A 65 kDa regulatory subunit; The PR65 subunit of protein phosphatase 2A serves as a scaffolding molecule to coordinate the assembly of the catalytic subunit and a variable regulatory B subunit
annotationB: FGFR1 oncogene partner 2 homolog; It is involved in the biological process described with: positive regulation of Ras protein signal transduction; positive regulation of ERK1 and ERK2 cascade; Belongs to the SIKE family
